::CyberShark::

    He was eating his food when he noticed something. It was a small insect 
crawling around the table. He squashed it. Getting up becasue he was 
disgusted to eat his food he walked over to the trash and threw it in. He 
noticed two more in the trash. (They are insects after all) He went into the 
kitchen to grab a drink and noticed somemore by a vent. He went to a computer 
monitor.
    "Computer give me a schimatic of the ktichen," One popped up before him 
on the screen. He pointed on the screen. "Where does that vent lead to?"
    "To many options to choose from, please specify." The computet replied. 
    "Just show me all of where it leads to," The computer did as it was told. 
The vent ran pratically through all of the ship, and to the outside. He 
picked up a bug and asked the computer to show where all organic life forms 
were in the ship. It showed that there were none in the kitchen, including 
other places. The strange part was that he had one in his hand, and could see 
a few more by a vent. But there were few organic creatures in the base at 
all. Only by the main door.
    "Battera, I will be right back, I'm going to find Magmatron." CyberShark 
said and rushed out the door. He made his way to the Control room, but 
Magmatron was not there.
    He asked the computer where Magmatron is. It showed him. He ran toward 
Magmatron.
    "Sir, I found this bug in the kitchen," CyberShark said out of breath. He 
needed to catch his breath before he could explain.
    "Yes, we seem to be having an infestation problem. It's nothing of 
importance. Yet." Magmatron replied.
    "But sir you don't understand, there no--urgk," CyberShark said as 
Magmatron lifted him off the ground by his neck.
    "Don't tell me what I don't understand. Do yoy understand that?" 
Magmatron said putting him down.
    "Yes sir. But the Computer doesn't show them as organic creatures. They 
are machines." CyberShark said.

(I could go further, but I wanna see what Phobia does with this news.)
